8 SECTION 4. AMENDATORY 17 O.S. 2021, Section 503, is
9 amended to read as follows:
10 Section 503. A. The Corporation Commission is hereby vested
11 with jurisdiction over the following:
12 1. The drilling for and or production of brine for commercial
13 purposes;
14 2. Class V injection wells used for the injection or disposal
15 of mineral brines as defined in the federal Safe Drinking Water Act
16 and 40 CFR Part 146; and
17 3. Class V wells used to inject spent brine into the same
18 formation from which it was withdrawn after extraction of halogens
19 or their salts as defined in 40 CFR Part 146.
20 B. The Commission may promulgate such rules that:
21 1. As are Are reasonably necessary to effectuate the purposes
22 of this act, including rules governing the drilling of production,
23 injection or disposal wells and the injection of effluent into
24 underground formations; and
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - HB4338 SFLR Page 11
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 2. To ensure Ensure that the drilling, casing and plugging of
2 wells is done in such a manner as to prevent the escape of brine and
3 effluent from one formation to another and to prevent the pollution
4 of fresh water supplies throughout the state.
5 C. The enforcement and adherence to the Oklahoma Brine
6 Development Act shall not apply to nor shall the Corporation
7 Commission have jurisdiction over Class I, III, IV or V wells
8 regulated by the Department of Environmental Quality pursuant to the
9 federal Safe Drinking Water Act and 40 CFR Parts 144 through 148,
10 inclusive, and the Oklahoma Environmental Quality Act.
11 SECTION 5. AMENDATORY 17 O.S. 2021, Section 504, is
12 amended to read as follows:
13 Section 504. A. A party desiring to unitize brine or produced
14 water rights shall file with the Corporation Commission an
15 application setting forth a description of the proposed brine
16 production unit or produced water unit area with a map or plat
17 thereof attached. The application shall allege the existence of the
18 facts required to be found by the Commission as provided in Section
19 7 506 of this act title and allege that the party desiring to
20 unitize the brine or produced water rights meets the criteria of
21 subparagraphs a and b of paragraph 10 of Section 502 of this title.
22 The application shall set forth the name and address of each brine
23 owner within the area affected by the application. Each such person
24 shall be a respondent to the application. In an application to
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - HB4338 SFLR Page 12
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 enla rge the brine production unit or produced water unit area, brine
2 owners within the existing unit and brine owners in the area to be
3 added to the unit shall be respondents to the application.
4 B. In the event the brine sought to be unitized in a proposed
5 brine production unit is found in association with solution gas, the
6 application shall set forth the name and address of each solution
7 gas owner within the area affected by the application. Each such
8 person shall be a respondent to the application. In an application
9 to enlarge the brine production unit area, solution gas owners
10 within the existing brine production unit and solution gas owners in
11 the area to be added to the brine production unit shall be
12 respondents to the application.
13 C. Every application to establish a brine production unit or
14 produced water unit shall have attached thereto a recommended plan
15 of unitization applicable to the proposed unit area.
